- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with predicting interactions between individuals and uses a link stream formalism to capture the dynamic of the system. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper discusses a protocol for activity prediction using supervised learning methods. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with social interactions between individuals. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses supervised learning methods to model the dynamic of the system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with capturing both the structural and temporal aspects of interactions, which involves data structures and algorithms.
